Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees.

> For extra crispy sweet potatoes, place the baking sheet in the oven while it preheats!

Place the @quinoa{3%ounce} in a #medium pot{} with 1 cup water and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to a simmer and cook for ~{20-25%minutes}, until tender. Add a splash of water if necessary. Set aside.

Meanwhile, peel and cut the @sweet potato{1}(peeled and cut into 1/2-inch cubes). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a pinch of salt and @black pepper{pinch} and @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Roast for about ~{15%minutes}, until tender and slightly caramelized.

Using a #small paring knife{}, remove the peel from the @orange{1}(peeled), carefully cutting around the flesh. Once peeled, hold the orange in one hand cut between the white membranes to remove the orange segments. Squeeze the remaining orange core into a #medium bowl{} to collect the juice.

Make the dressing: add @Dijon mustard{1%tablespoon} and the juice of half a @lemon{1}(halved) to the orange juice. Whisk in @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Halve, peel and pit the @avocado{1}(peeled and sliced), then thinly slice.

Plate the quinoa. Toss the @arugula{2%ounce} with half the dressing and place atop quinoa. Add the avocado, orange segments, roasted sweet potato, @feta cheese{1/4%cup}, and @almonds{1%ounce}(sliced). Drizzle with remaining dressing. Enjoy!